Introduction

This script is set to carry out QC visualization and filtering of Visium slides so as to prepare them for subsequent analysis. We use as a reference QC workflow the one shown in STutility ## Libraries

# install_github('linxihui/NNLM')
# devtools::install_github(
#     "jbergenstrahle/STUtility"
# )

library(Seurat)
# library(STutility)
library(ggpubr)
library(cowplot)
library(dplyr)
library(ggplot2)
library(stringr)
library(readr)
# library(tidyverse)

Setting parameters

Loading necessary paths and parameters

source("misc/paths.R")
source("utils/bin.R")
plt_dir <- sprintf("%s/%s", qc_32, plt_dir)
robj_dir <- sprintf("%s/%s", qc_32, robj_dir)

dir.create(path = plt_dir,
           showWarnings = FALSE,
           recursive = TRUE)

dir.create(path = robj_dir,
           showWarnings = FALSE,
           recursive = TRUE)
sample_id <- params$sample_id
# sample_id <- "c28w2r_7jne4i"
# THRESHOLDS
# min_lib_size <- 500
# min_n_genes <- 50
# max_pct_mt <- 50
# min_cells <- 8
min_lib_size <- qc_dict[[sample_id]][["min_lib_size"]]
min_n_genes <- qc_dict[[sample_id]][["min_n_genes"]]
max_pct_mt <- qc_dict[[sample_id]][["max_pct_mt"]]
min_cells <- qc_dict[[sample_id]][["min_cells"]]

Load data

We have 4 different datasets that we are going to analyze separately. In each Rmarkdown notebook we analyze 1 dataset.

spaceranger_data <- sprintf("%s/%s/outs",
                           space_ranger, sample_id)
se_obj <- Seurat::Load10X_Spatial(data.dir = spaceranger_data,
                                  filename = "filtered_feature_bc_matrix.h5",
                                  assay = "Spatial",
                                  slice = sample_id,
                                  filter.matrix = FALSE)

Add mitochondrial and ribosomal %

# Collect all genes coded on the mitochondrial genome
se_obj[["percent.mito"]] <- Seurat::PercentageFeatureSet(object = se_obj, pattern = "^MT-")

# Collect all genes coding for ribosomal proteins
se_obj[["percent.ribo"]] <- Seurat::PercentageFeatureSet(object = se_obj, pattern = "^RPL|^RPS")

QC Analysis

Basic features

Next we plot some basic features that will help us visualize and define filtering options.

plt_ls <- qc_hist_plots(se = se_obj,
                         nfeat = "nFeature_Spatial",
                         ncount = "nCount_Spatial",
                         slot = "counts",
                         assay = "Spatial")

cowplot::plot_grid(plotlist = plt_ls, ncol = 2)

Next, lets look at how these features are distributed spatially.

plt_st_ls <- qc_st_plots(se = se_obj,
                         nfeat = "nFeature_Spatial",
                         ncount = "nCount_Spatial",
                         slot = "counts",
                         assay = "Spatial")

cowplot::plot_grid(plotlist = plt_st_ls, ncol = 2)

Feature covariation

Next we look at how these features covariate.

plt_covar_ls <- qc_covar_plots(se = se_obj,
                               nfeat = "nFeature_Spatial",
                               ncount = "nCount_Spatial",
                               slot = "counts",
                               assay = "Spatial")

Filtering spots

No need to fitler out any bad quality spots.

Save RDS

Save the object to use downstream.

saveRDS(object = se_obj,
        file = sprintf("%s/qc_se_%s.rds", robj_dir, sample_id))
